(267, 'default', 'Updated event: MEMA 2026 — Myogenic Excellence Music Awards Gala', 'App\\Models\\Event\\Event', NULL, 66, 'App\\Models\\User', 1, '{\"changes\": {\"updated_at\": \"2026-03-26 15:09:04\", \"description\": \"The Vision\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Myogenic Excellence Music Awards — MEMA — was born from a simple but powerful conviction: African gospel music is world-class, and its creators deserve a world-class platform to be recognised. Kenya\'s gospel music scene has produced artists, producers, directors, and photographers whose work has touched millions of lives across the continent and beyond. MEMA 2026 is the inaugural celebration of that excellence.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhat to Expect on the Night\\r\\n\\r\\nThe MEMA Gala 2026 is a full black-tie gala evening held at the Radisson Blu Hotel & Convention Centre, Nairobi, on September 16, 2026. Doors open at 4:30 PM with a red carpet reception and networking cocktails. The main ceremony begins at 7:00 PM and features live gospel performances by nominated artists, a sit-down gala dinner, and the presentation of all MEMA awards across three awards blocks. The evening concludes with an after-gala celebration and group photography with award winners.\\r\\n\\r\\nHow Nominations and Voting Work\\r\\n\\r\\nAnyone can nominate a gospel artist, producer, director, or photographer they believe deserves recognition. Nominations are submitted online, reviewed by the MEMA team, and shortlisted nominees are published for public voting. The nomination window runs from April 16 to July 15, 2026. Public voting opens August 1 and closes September 14, 2026 — giving the gospel music community the power to crown their champions before the big night.\\r\\n\\r\\nTickets\\r\\n\\r\\nTickets are available in multiple tiers to suit individual guests, couples, organisations, and corporate tables — from Early Bird Regular Seats (KES 1,000) to VVIP Tables for 10 (KES 50,000). All tickets include a gala dinner and event programme. VIP and VVIP tickets include priority seating, VIP lounge access, and meet & greet opportunities with award winners.\\r\\n\\r\\nBe Part of the Story\\r\\n\\r\\nMEMA 2026 is more than an event — it is a movement. Whether you are nominating an artist you believe in, casting your vote, attending the gala, or sponsoring a category, you are part of something historic. This is the beginning of a new chapter for gospel music recognition in Africa.\", \"event_category_id\": \"1\"}}', NULL, '2026-03-26 12:09:04', '2026-03-26 12:09:04'),
